Logistic Regression Classification - Extended

Mervin M Fansler

11 July 2023

Purpose

Here we attempt using covariates to classify genes into localization groups.

Initialization

Libraries

library(magrittr)
library(tidyverse)
library(ggtern)
library(broom)
library(caret)
library(nnet)
library(readxl)
library(writexl)

Data

Loading

df_tiger <- readRDS(RDS_IN)

Preprocessing

Subset

df_data <- select(df_tiger, category, all_of(COVARIATES))

Imputing

df_imputed <- df_data %>%
    mutate_at(c("Anno_3UTR_length", "mane_mRNA_length", "mane_mean_cds_exon_length_all"), 
              ~ ifelse(is.na(.x), median(.x, na.rm=TRUE), .x)) %>%
    mutate_at(-1, ~ ifelse(is.na(.x), 0, .x))

Data Normalizing

df_scaled <- mutate_at(df_imputed, -1, ~ scale(sqrt(.x))[,1])

Splitting

idx_train <- createDataPartition(df_scaled$category, p=0.8, list=FALSE)

df_train <- df_scaled[idx_train,]
df_test  <- df_scaled[-idx_train,]

full_join(count(df_train, category, name="n_train"),
          count(df_test, category, name="n_test"),
          by="category") %>%
    knitr::kable()
category n_train n_test
DF 2696 673
ER 736 183
TG 997 249
CY 1185 296

Export

outfile <- sprintf("tbl/%s-model-fit-lr-extend.xlsx", format(Sys.time(), '%Y%m%d'))
tidy(model) %>%
    arrange(p.value) %>%
    write_xlsx(outfile)

Model Accuracy

mean(predict(model, df_test) == df_test$category)
## [1] 0.5474661

Coefficients

coefficients(model) %>%
    as_tibble(rownames="category") %>%
    select(-c("(Intercept)")) %>%
    pivot_longer(-c("category"), names_to="variable", values_to="value") %>%
    mutate(variable=fct_reorder(variable, abs(value), max)) %>%
    ggplot(aes(y=variable, x=value, fill=category)) +
    geom_vline(xintercept=0) +
    geom_bar(stat='identity', position='dodge', color='black', size=0.1, width=0.9) +
    scale_fill_manual(values=LOC_COLORS) +
    labs(x="Coefficient", y=NULL, fill="Category") +
    theme_light()

ggsave("img/extend/lr-coefs-all.pdf", width=6, height=8, dpi=300)

Coefficient Pairs

TIAL1, TIS11B

df_train %>% 
    summarize(across(everything(), mean)) %>% 
    slice(rep(1, N_STEPS)) %>%
    mutate(TIA1_L1_CLIP=seq(-10, 10, length.out=N_STEPS)) %>%
    slice(rep(1:N_STEPS, times=N_STEPS)) %>%
    mutate(TIS11B_CLIP=rep(seq(-10,10, length.out=N_STEPS), each=N_STEPS)) %>%
    mutate(category=predict(object=model, .)) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=TIA1_L1_CLIP, y=TIS11B_CLIP, fill=category)) +
    geom_tile(linejoin="bevel") +
